1. Use PEP 8 style guide for code formatting.
2. Prefer f-strings for string formatting.
3. Use type hints for function parameters and return values.
4. Write docstrings for all functions and classes using Google-style docstrings.
5. Use list comprehensions and generator expressions where appropriate.
6. Prefer 'with' statements for file and resource management.
7. Use virtual environments for project dependencies.
8. Follow the Zen of Python principles.
9. Use snake_case for function and variable names, and PascalCase for class names.
10. Implement error handling using try-except blocks where necessary.
11. Use built-in functions and standard library modules when possible.
